Imagine:

You are standing at your home ðŸ .

The park ðŸŽ¡ is 5 meters east from you.

You can describe that as:

"Go 5 meters towards the East."

ðŸ‘‰ This is a vector â€” something that tells both direction and distance.

ðŸ§© In Simple Words:------------

A vector = direction + distance (magnitude)
So if I say:
Vector = (5, 0, 0)
It means:
Move 5 units in the X direction (right)
0 in Y (no up/down)
0 in Z (no forward/backward)

Example i Code  : -
public Transform homeObject;
public Transform parkObject;

void Start()
{
    Vector3 home = homeObject.position;
    Vector3 park = parkObject.position;

    Vector3 direction = park - home;

    Debug.Log(direction);
}

Notes:-
This formula ALWAYS remember:
  --> direction = final - initial

